# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Model provider configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the provider you want to use.
# The app picks a provider in this order:
#   1. Local LLM         -> if LOCAL_LLM_BASE_URL is set (takes priority)
#   2. Anthropic Claude  -> if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is a real key
#   3. Mock provider     -> otherwise (canned responses, no network calls)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Option 1: Local LLM (OpenAI-compatible endpoint) ------------------------
# Works with Ollama, LM Studio, llama.cpp (llama-server), vLLM,
# text-generation-webui, and anything else exposing the OpenAI HTTP API.
#
# IMPORTANT: include the API path suffix the server expects (usually "/v1").
#
#   Ollama        -> http://localhost:11434/v1   (model e.g. "llama3.1", "qwen3-coder:30b")
#   LM Studio     -> http://localhost:1234/v1    (model = the name shown in LM Studio)
#   llama.cpp     -> http://localhost:8080/v1    (model can be any string)
#   vLLM          -> http://localhost:8000/v1    (model = the served model id)
#
# Uncomment and adjust to enable a local model:
# LOCAL_LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# LOCAL_LLM_MODEL=qwen3-coder:30b
# LOCAL_LLM_API_KEY=not-needed

# --- Option 2: Hosted Anthropic Claude ---------------------------------------
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
